meanings.definition: To move faster than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The cheetah outspeeds the turtle in a race.
meanings.sent2: The car outspeeds the bicycle on the highway.
meanings.sent3: The rabbit outspeeds the snail, making the snail jealous.
meanings.sent4: His determination outspeeds any obstacle in his path.
meanings.sent5: The wind outspeeds all other elements, rushing through the trees.

meanings.sent1: The new sports car outspeeds the old model in acceleration.
meanings.sent2: The athlete outspeeds his competitors in the final sprint.
meanings.sent3: The student outspeeds the teacher in solving the math problem.
meanings.sent4: Her wit outspeeds any opponent in a battle of words.
meanings.sent5: The spaceship outspeeds any aircraft, reaching the stars in record time.
